text: The Honnametti bush frog (Roarchestes honnametti) is a frog. It lives in India, Bangladesh, and China. Scientists think it could also live in Myanmar. Scientists have seen it 1272 meters above sea level. The adult male frog is 16.1â€“20.0 mm long from nose to rear end. It has disks on all its toes for climbing. The disks are orange in color. There is only some webbed skin on its feet. The skin of the frog's back is brown in color. The iris of the eye is gold-brown in color. The tops of the back legs are orange with black stripes. The bottoms of the legs are brown with black and white spots. ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
title: Raorchestes cangyuanensis
